body:
Configuration that enables ES2022 syntax and globals is:

```js
{
   "parserOptions": {
      "ecmaVersion": 2022
   },
   "env": {
      "es2021": true
   } 
}
```

There's still no difference between ES2022 and ES2021 globals, so we haven't added `es2022` environment yet.

All available environments are listed here: https://eslint.org/docs/user-guide/configuring/language-options#specifying-environments

Currently available ES environments are: `es6`, `es2017`, `es2020`, and `es2021`.

With the new config system (https://github.com/eslint/eslint/issues/13481), there will be a single setting `languageOptions.ecmaVersion` to enable both syntax and globals (for example, `"languageOptions" :  { "ecmaVersion": 2022 }` enables ES2022 syntax and ES2022 globals). The concept of enviroments will be removed.

That said, I agree it's confusing that `es2022` and other years are missing, and I wouldn't mind adding those environments now. @eslint/eslint-tsc thoughts about this?
